    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/credibility-assessment-team-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factors achieving levels below required thresholds and six factors flagged as epistemic gaps, the assessment team accepted the package on the basis that the Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification verification activity (declared via hasVerificationActivity) provides sufficient coverage of input uncertainty for the three primary parameters. The team noted that the declared UQ verification activity supports the overall uncertainty characterization argument and that residual gaps are bounded by conservative clinical threshold margins. Accepted with conditions pending resolution of model form and use error gaps prior to regulatory submission.",
